_**This post is part of our special coverage[Indigenous
Rights](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/indigenous-rights/).**_

The [previously featured Creative Commons
documentary](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2012/03/22/argentina-documentary-
on-the-indigenous-people-in-buenos-aires/ "Global Voices article on Runa
Kuti") Runa Kuti on the identity of urban dwelling indigenous descendants in
the city of Buenos Aires is looking for volunteers to help them subtitle the
documentary into indigenous languages found in Argentina such Quechua, Aymara,
Mapuche and Guaraní as well as into English.

On their blog they've posted their [call for
volunteers](http://runakuti.blogspot.com.ar/2012/04/se-buscan-subtitulos.html
"Runa Kuti call for volunteer subtitlers"):

> Quien quiera, tenga ganas, tiempo, ocio, curiosidad, computadora, internet y
> otros idiomas para apoyarnos se los agradeceremos añadiendolos a los
> créditos del documental y mandándoles buenas vibras, donde quiera que
> estemos y donde quiera que estén.
>
> Todos los idiomas son bienvenidos pero guardamos un especial interés por el
> quechua, aymara y guaraní.

Whomever wants to, feels like it, has time, as a hobby, out of curiousity, has
a computer, internet and other languages to help us we will thank them by
adding them to the documentary credits and sending good vibes their way,
wherever we are and wherever they are.

All languages are welcome but we hold a special interest for Quechua, Aymara
and Guaraní.

<http://vimeo.com/32219379>

The [trailer
](http://www.universalsubtitles.org/es/videos/kA4QC83Yopk4/info/trailer-runa-
kuti-indigenas-urbanos/ "Runa Kuti trailer to subtitle")has been subtitled
into Spanish, French, English and Portuguese, the [full length
documentary](http://www.universalsubtitles.org/es/videos/ikOQKW0swGVS/info/runa-
kuti-indigenas-urbanos/ "Subtitle Runa Kuti Documentary") has the full
transcription in Spanish.

<http://vimeo.com/37754616>

